# Per-host deploy values for Deploy-DayZServer.ps1. This file describes the SERVER — every
# key here gets rendered into something that lives and runs ON that box. It is NOT where you
# tell your dev machine how to reach the server; that's dev-machine-local info and belongs in
# deployer.env (copy deployer.env.example) instead — see docs/CONFIGURATION.md.
#
# Copy this to `host.env` on each host and set the values for THAT host. Deploy renders
# the systemd unit templates ({{DEPLOY_USER}}/{{DEPLOY_GROUP}}/{{DEPLOY_HOME}}) with
# these, so the same deploy/ payload is drift-clean everywhere.
#
# Not part of the deploy payload (like map.env). If host.env is absent, Deploy falls
# back to the built-in defaults, which are these VPS values — EXCEPT DEPLOY_SERVER_PASSWORD,
# DEPLOY_ADMIN_PASSWORD, and DEPLOY_STEAM_ACCOUNT, which have no default and make Deploy
# refuse to run until set (secrets, and an identifier that must never be baked into the
# tracked repo/scripts).
#
# KEY=VALUE only, one per line (no inline comments).

DEPLOY_USER=ubuntu
DEPLOY_GROUP=ubuntu
DEPLOY_HOME=/home/ubuntu

# serverDZ.cfg's join/admin passwords ({{DEPLOY_SERVER_PASSWORD}}/{{DEPLOY_ADMIN_PASSWORD}}).
# host.env is gitignored and never rsynced between hosts, so this is the only place
# these live. CHANGE THESE — don't ship the example values.
#
# OPEN SERVER: leave DEPLOY_SERVER_PASSWORD empty (keep the key, drop the value) to run a
# no-password server anyone can join — it renders as `password = "";`. The KEY must stay
# present; deleting the line entirely makes Apply-ServerCfg refuse (an absent key reads as an
# unconfigured host, not a deliberate open server). DEPLOY_ADMIN_PASSWORD must NOT be empty.
#   open server:  DEPLOY_SERVER_PASSWORD=
DEPLOY_SERVER_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME
DEPLOY_ADMIN_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME

# Steam account that OWNS DayZ — steamcmd can't download the dedicated server app
# anonymously. Rendered into update.sh at deploy time; never baked into the tracked script.
DEPLOY_STEAM_ACCOUNT=your_steam_account

# How often the auto-update checker compares the installed server build to Steam's latest
# and arms a deferred update if behind (applied on the next server start). A systemd time
# span: 4h, 90min, 1d, etc. Set to 'off' to disable the periodic check entirely — the
# manual update trigger (API `update` action) still works. Each check opens a Steam session
# for the account above, so keep it modest. Default: 4h.
DEPLOY_UPDATE_CHECK_INTERVAL=4h

# --- NOT set here: which host to deploy TO — see deployer.env.example instead ---
